Stemming: Rule-based chopping of word endings to get a rough root, e.g., “playing”, “played” → “play” or “play”.

Lemmatization: Uses vocabulary + POS to get the correct base word (lemma), e.g., “better” → “good”, “cars” → “car”.

Other short important ones:

Tokenization: Splitting text into smaller units (words, subwords, characters) that the model can process.

Stop words: Very common words (like “is”, “the”, “and”) often removed as they add little meaning.

Bag of Words (BoW): Text representation using word counts, ignoring order and grammar.

TF-IDF: Weighted BoW that downweights common words and upweights rare but informative words.

Overfitting: Model learns noise/memory of training data, performs poorly on new data.

Underfitting: Model too simple, performs poorly on both train and test data.

Precision: Of the predicted positives, how many are actually positive.

Recall: Of all actual positives, how many did the model correctly find.

F1-score: Harmonic mean of precision and recall, balances both in one metric.
